frameDefinitions: A Reader visually examines a Text, typically in a linear order, to understand its content.
An Agent becomes involved in an Issue which has negative consequences for them.
This frame involves Buyers paying Money for Goods.
These are words describing a basic commercial transaction involving a Buyer and a Seller exchanging Money and Goods, taking the perspective of the Buyer.
A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
The Reader attends to a Text to process its information.
frameExamples: I <t>paid</t> her $50 for a video game.
Abby bought a car from Robin for $5,000.
We are <t>renting</t> our apartment from a kind man named Tom.
I <t>read</t> A Tale of Two Cities last night.
